  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>This article\u00a0addresses how to handle items on a\u00a0Return Repair (rework)\u00a0ticket that you wish to discount instead of waiving the full charge.</p><p>There are a number of Return Repair (rework) scenarios that could occur, and we have a detailed walkthrough for the\u00a0most\u00a0common ways that return repairs (reworks) are handled.</p><p>1. choose one of the following scenarios:</p><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933606988/Performing+a+Return+Repair+Rework+for+the+Same+Repair+Service\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933606988\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Return repair (rework) for the same repair service</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933770925/Performing+a+Return+Repair+rework+for+a+Different+Repair+Service\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933770925\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Return repair (rework) for a different repair service</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933639775/Performing+a+Return+Repair+Rework+to+Replace+a+Defective+Part\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933639775\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Return Repair (rework) to replace a defective part</a>  </p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933508711/Performing+a+Return+Repair+Rework+Ticket+Without+the+Original+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933508711\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">How To: Waive Charges for Return Repairs Without the Original Ticket</a></p></li></ul><p /><p>2. You can add an item\u00a0to a Return Repair ticket one of two ways: by adding a replacement item, or by adding a new item to the ticket and waiving the charge.</p><p /><p><strong>Adding a Replacement Item</strong></p><p>a. Select the\u00a0item(s) from the &quot;Replacement Items&quot; list on a new\u00a0Return Repair ticket by clicking on the &quot;Replace Item&quot; button for the item(s).</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803577/Return%20Repair%20Discounted%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>b. Next, click the &quot;Apply\u00a0Charge&quot; button for the item, to apply the normal price for the item.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933803577/Return%20Repair%20Discounted%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>c. Next, apply the discount to the item according to your policy for return repairs.</p><p /><p><strong>Adding a new item, and\u00a0applying a discount</strong></p><p>a. Add a new item to the ticket using the ticket one of the scan / search / lookup methods.</p><p>b. Next, simply apply the discount to the item according to your policy for return repairs.</p>",
